Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.85,0:02:53.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.02,0:02:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Masumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.06,0:02:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Where in the world have you been?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.93,0:03:00.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Masumi?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.68,0:03:02.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.97,0:03:07.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my... what did she drag in with her?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.75,0:03:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Is that water I hear?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.49,0:03:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You came here to ask us \Nhow our daughter's doing?{a direct response to a question he asked off-screen, probably "How is your daughter doing?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.29,0:04:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, it's true that she hasn't \Nbeen feeling well lately.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:02.63,0:04:05.44,Default,,0,0,0,,But... we already know the reason for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.15,0:04:08.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's something neither \Ndoctor nor mushi-shi can cure.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.73,0:04:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The fellow she liked stopped visiting her, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.21,0:04:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,She's been very depressed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.61,0:04:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Even her health is suffering because of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.91,0:04:23.22,Default,,0,0,0,,But she gets this way every time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.15,0:04:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This one {\i1}is{\i0} taking a bit longer than usual, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.89,0:04:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the cause this time may be different.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.85,0:04:35.70,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.41,0:04:41.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Before I explain, can you please \Nbring me a basin filled with water?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.32,0:04:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Try looking at your reflection in this.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:58.81,0:05:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Her mirror image has been stolen away.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.41,0:05:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.39,0:05:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,There are mushi that live in still ponds called Mizukagami, or "Water Mirror" mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.95,0:05:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,They blend in because they resemble quicksilver.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.41,0:05:17.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When one of these mushi reflects \Nthe image of an animal passing by,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.42,0:05:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,it comes ashore and tries to imitate that animal's appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.79,0:05:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It proceeds to follow the "original" around.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.05,0:05:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,This, in turn, causes the animal to gradually become weaker.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.01,0:05:35.87,Default,,0,0,0,,The weaker the animal gets, the more concrete the Mizukagami's form becomes...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.33,0:05:38.46,Default,,0,0,0,,until the animal loses its \Nphysical form completely.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.67,0:05:41.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Once that happens,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.04,0:05:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the Mizukagami takes the \Nplace of the original animal.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.53,0:05:48.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Mizukagami need various minerals from water in order to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:48.71,0:05:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Once one gains a physical form, it will search \Nfor bodies of water with higher mineral content.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.05,0:05:58.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In its true form, a Mizukagami \Ncannot move of its own volition.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.03,0:06:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of this, it covets a body \Nthat can freely search for what it needs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.31,0:06:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,We can't let that happen!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.55,0:06:06.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't there something we can do?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.83,0:06:12.44,Default,,0,0,0,,At the moment when a Mizukagami tries to replace the original, it becomes fully visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.49,0:06:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If the original shows the Mizukagami its own reflection in a mirror at the instant of its transition,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.72,0:06:19.98,Default,,0,0,0,,it will lose its form, \Nand the original will return to normal.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:19.98,0:06:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that all? Sounds easy enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.53,0:06:26.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Masumi, you have a hand mirror, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.66,0:06:27.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Where'd you put it?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.45,0:06:34.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What's with it? It's so dirty \Nthat you can't see anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.52,0:06:35.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, I'll polish it for—{length}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.69,0:06:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.29,0:06:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This mirror... is very important to me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.39,0:06:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll do it myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.91,0:07:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, I'll be back in a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.92,0:07:20.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.85,0:07:25.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where are you going? Masumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.31,0:07:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It's dirty again already?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.47,0:08:01.30,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't ever polish it, because I want {\i1}you{\i0} to.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.49,0:08:10.49,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking, Masumi...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.49,0:08:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.39,0:08:16.94,Default,,0,0,0,,These days, there just aren't that many people who need their mirrors polished around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.17,0:08:21.56,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been thinking of looking for work elsewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.65,0:08:23.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.15,0:08:27.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But then... when would I get to see you next?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.27,0:08:29.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Who knows?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.44,0:08:31.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know when I'll be back.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.59,0:08:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.59,0:08:35.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not like I want this either...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.53,0:08:39.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but I've got to provide for myself somehow, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.93,0:08:41.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Please try to understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.93,0:08:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.33,0:08:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll wait for you in your new village!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.94,0:08:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll become your bride!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.38,0:08:51.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to settle down yet.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.48,0:08:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll wait until you {\i1}do{\i0} want to!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.98,0:08:55.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Please...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.65,0:08:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but I don't want a tomboy like you for a wife.{what an ass}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.69,0:09:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd prefer someone who's got a gentler disposition.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.55,0:09:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.87,0:09:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can't say when I'll come see you again.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:15.11,0:09:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, the next time the mirror gets dirty,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.20,0:09:19.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but just polish it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.41,0:10:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,What am I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.13,0:11:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.59,0:11:28.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really want to become me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.83,0:11:34.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You want to become someone like me, of all people?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.39,0:11:45.30,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks like you can hear \Nthe Mizukagami's footsteps now.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.49,0:11:51.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Polished your hand mirror yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.65,0:11:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Unless you want the Mizukagami to take your place,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.14,0:11:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you'd better do it soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.45,0:12:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't matter if it takes my place.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.77,0:12:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.27,0:12:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no point in being here anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.37,0:12:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If it wants to be me so much, it can go ahead.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.87,0:12:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Listen... If you throw your life away like this,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.96,0:12:17.17,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll lose even the {\i1}capacity{\i0} to feel regret.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.87,0:12:20.11,Default,,0,0,0,,If you let the Mizukagami switch places with you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.11,0:12:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you will lose not only your body, \Nbut also your consciousness itself.{comma for emphasis}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.41,0:12:29.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You will become a mere "thing"—incapable of having any significant effect on this world{ through your free will}.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.25,0:12:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A thing that won't matter, whether it exists or not?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.55,0:12:39.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.97,0:12:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't really see much of a difference, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.47,0:12:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No matter how hard I tried not to be, \NI was meaningless to him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.11,0:13:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't matter what I said or what I did.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.49,0:13:07.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no influence over him.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:09.79,0:13:14.04,Default,,0,0,0,,It didn't matter whether I existed or not then, and it doesn't matter now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.09,0:13:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,That world you're in right now... It's lonely, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.23,0:13:33.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But you know, there's a world \Neven more lonely than that one.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.51,0:13:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the world that's home to the entities lacking a physical form, like mushi.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.57,0:13:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It is where the things unwanted \Nby the world writhe in the darkness.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.61,0:13:50.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Mushi may lack souls,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.95,0:13:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but many of them nevertheless try to \Ncrawl out of the darkness in search of the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.37,0:13:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how lonely that world is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.97,0:14:08.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mizukagami are so fragile that they disappear just by seeing their reflection{by its original} in a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.77,0:14:12.73,Default,,0,0,0,,That in itself is a testament to the power of those with a physical form—
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.73,0:14:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,the power gained simply by having a body of flesh and blood.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.87,0:14:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,However, once you switch places, your positions will be reversed.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.53,0:14:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you really want to return \Nto a world that feels less lonely,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.53,0:14:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,you must protect yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.17,0:15:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Her pulse has gotten very weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.05,0:15:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Polished your mirror yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.05,0:15:45.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.65,0:15:49.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Good.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.80,0:15:51.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Now all you have to do is keep it close.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.99,0:15:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn't be long before the Mizukagami appears.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.95,0:15:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,At that moment, you must use the mirror to reflect it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.55,0:15:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Don't miss it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.07,0:16:06.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.65,0:16:09.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Um... I have to go to the restroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.03,0:16:11.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you sure you can go by yourself?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.41,0:16:26.92,Default,,0,0,0,,I knew he'd come back.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.94,0:16:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,He's not here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.25,0:18:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's gone!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.01,0:18:20.53,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It's all the way over there!{how did even bounce that far}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.09,0:18:27.04,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I feel so weak...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.84,0:18:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Am I...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.85,0:18:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}going to get replaced?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.65,0:18:47.82,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Will I become...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.33,0:18:55.84,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}something that can only follow others around?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.82,0:18:59.78,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}No...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.58,0:19:03.12,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I don't want that to happen.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.91,0:19:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}What is wrong with you?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.63,0:19:09.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop pretending to be me!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.85,0:19:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm fine now, I swear!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.66,0:19:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Not another word, you foolish girl!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.94,0:19:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,At the very least, you've got to rest for today!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.60,0:19:52.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.95,0:19:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Why did it vanish like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.43,0:20:01.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, I've been wondering that myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.49,0:20:07.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.99,0:20:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It was your eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.39,0:20:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The Mizukagami must have been reflected in your eyes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.27,0:20:15.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Who'd have thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.57,0:20:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,As long as you keep your eyes open, you don't even need a mirror.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.89,0:20:26.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess that, too, is a testament to how much power we possess just by having physical form.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.53,0:20:30.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is something wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.21,0:20:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't notice until now...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.59,0:20:36.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but you're not half bad looking!{lol}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.49,0:20:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:38.95,0:20:41.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Your hair's such a weird color. \NDoes it run in the family?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.26,0:20:42.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you married?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.52,0:20:43.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Where did you grow up?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.97,0:20:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems she's already recovered fully.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.26,0:20:48.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That it does.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.39,0:20:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Well then, I think it's time I get going.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.16,0:20:52.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.16,0:20:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Can't you stay just a little longer?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.63,0:20:56.34,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got to show my thanks!{lol innuendo}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.34,0:20:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Masumi!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.36,0:20:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When will you ever learn?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.27,0:21:24.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.19,0:21:42.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I figured that you would return to this place.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.47,0:21:44.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Come with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.64,0:21:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll guide you to a better lake \Nthat's deeper in the mountains.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.29,0:21:50.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not giving up my body, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.39,0:21:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't look so lonely.
